Pan-seared Romaine

1 romaine heart
1 tablespoon olive oil
salt
Parmesan cheese
ranch dressing


Cut romaine in half, rinse in water, shake off and pat dry. 

Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a 12-inch cast-iron skillet.  Add two romaine
halves cut side down and cook for five minutes.  Flip to the other
side and cook for three more minutes.  Transfer to a plate.  Add salt,
Parmesan cheese, and ranch dressing.
